{{COI|date=October 2016}} {{lowercase title}} {{Infobox company | name = goTenna | logo = File:GoTenna_Logo.png | logo_size = | logo_alt = | type = Privately held company | founded = {{start date|2012|11}} | founders = Daniela Perdomo, Jorge Perdomo | hq_location = Brooklyn, New York | hq_location_country = United States | industry = | products = | brands = goTenna, goTenna Mesh, goTenna Pro, goTenna Plus | website = {{URL|https://gotenna.com}} }}
'''goTenna''' (goTenna Inc.) is a [[Brooklyn, New York]]-based [[Startup company|startup]] that designs and develops technologies for [[off-grid]] and [[Decentralization|decentralized]] communications. goTenna devices pair with [[smartphones]] and, through intelligent [[Mobile ad-hoc networking|mobile ad hoc networking]] [[Communications protocol|protocols]], enable users to send [[Text messaging|texts]] and share locations on a [[peer-to-peer]] basis, foregoing the need for centralized communications infrastructure of any kind.<ref name=CNET>{{cite web|last1=Statt|first1=Nick|title=GoTenna creates a cell network out of thin air anywhere on Earth|url=http://www.cnet.com/news/gotenna-creates-cell-network-out-of-thin-air-anywhere-on-earth/|website=CNET.com|publisher=CNET|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref>
== History == The idea for goTenna came to siblings Daniela and Jorge Perdomo in November 2012 after [[Hurricane Sandy]] knocked out 25 percent of [[cell towers]], and caused outages for 25 percent of [[Internet]] services, across 10 states on the [[East Coast of the United States|East Coast]].<ref name=Wired>{{cite web|last1=Rhodes|first1=Margaret|title=A Pocket-Sized Antenna That Lets You Text Even in a Disaster Like Sandy|url=https://www.wired.com/2014/07/a-brilliant-antennae-that-lets-you-text-even-during-a-catastrophe-like-sandy/|website=wired.com|publisher=Wired|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="CNN Money">{{cite web|last1=Goldman|first1=David|title=Sandy knocks out 25% of cell service in its path|url=http://money.cnn.com/2012/10/31/technology/mobile/sandy-cell-service-outages/|website=money.cnn.com|publisher=CNN|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref> Officially incorporated in April 2013,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://icis.corp.delaware.gov/Ecorp/EntitySearch/NameSearch.aspx|title=Division of Corporations - Filing|website=icis.corp.delaware.gov|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref> the company’s stated goal is to build “people-powered peer-to-peer communication systems…reducing our reliance on cell towers and wifi routers, and providing anyone the ability to create a network on their terms.”<ref name="goTenna About Us">{{cite web|title=About Us|url=http://www.gotenna.com/pages/about-us|website=gotenna.com|publisher=goTenna|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref>
In September 2016, goTenna launched goTenna Plus, a, subscription-based upgrade to the goTenna applications, which includes the capability to use other goTenna users as gateways to relay messages through to traditional SMS networks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.outsideonline.com/2119336/new-gotenna-could-make-backcountry-safer-if-people-use-it|title=The New GoTenna Could Make the Backcountry Safer—If People Use It|last=Rose|first=Brent|date=2016-09-30|work=Outside Online|access-date=2017-04-19|language=en}}</ref> The company also released its [[software development kit]], enabling developers to create new applications using goTenna hardware.<ref name="BI 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/gotenna-portable-antenna-upgrade-2016-9|title=These portable antennas let you send texts with friends, even when you don't have service|website=businessinsider.com|publisher=Business Insider|last1=Weller|first1=Chris|accessdate=30 September 2016}}</ref> Around the same time, goTenna unveiled a second-generation device: goTenna Mesh, the first consumer-ready [[mesh network]] of its kind, available to 49 countries.<ref name="Flamm">{{Cite news|url=http://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20170418/TECHNOLOGY/170419882/sandy-inspired-texting-tool-now-helping-sandy-survivors-and-will-be-marketed-to-first-responders|title=Sandy-inspired texting tool now helping Sandy survivors|last=Flamm|first=Matthew|work=Crain's New York Business|access-date=2017-04-18}}</ref> In March 2017, the company announced its goTenna Pro line, for [[professional mobile radio]] communications needs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/03/27/gotenna-pro-meshing-radio-aspires-to-deploy-next-to-rescue-fire-and-security-teams/|title=GoTenna Pro meshing radio aspires to deploy next to rescue, fire and security teams|last=Coldewey|first=Devin|website=TechCrunch|access-date=2017-04-18}}</ref>
== Awards == * [[Consumer Electronics Show|CES]] Innovation Award 2017: Tech for a Better World<ref name=":0" /> * [[Consumer Electronics Show|CES]] Innovation Award 2017: Wireless Accessory<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=http://www.ces.tech/Events-Experiences/CES-Innovation-Awards-Program/CES-Innovation-Awards.aspx|website=ces.tech|publisher=CTA|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref> * [[Industrial Designers Society of America]] – [[International Design Excellence Awards|IDEA]] 2016 Gold<ref>{{cite web|title=Going for the Gold: #IDSAIDEA Reveals Global Design Winners|url=http://www.idsa.org/news/idea-news/going-gold-idsa-idea%C2%AE-2016-reveals-global-design-winners|website=www.idsa.org|publisher=Industrial Designers Society of America|accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref> * [[Edison Awards]] Gold – Innovative Services<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edisonawards.com/?gclid=CP6q9JbyoswCFUIfhgodxRwNqA|website=www.edisonawards.com|title=2016 Edison Awards Winners |accessdate=22 April 2016}}</ref> * [[Consumer Electronics Show|CES]] Innovation Award 2015: Tech for a Better World<ref name="CES">{{cite web|title=2015 CES Innovation Awards|url=http://content.ce.org/PDF/2015_CES_Innovations_Awards.pdf|website=CE.org|publisher=Consumer Electronics Association|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref> * [[Consumer Electronics Show|CES]] Innovation Award 2015: Wireless Accessory<ref name="CES" /> * [[Fast Company (magazine)|Fast Company]] 2015 Innovation by Design<ref name="Fast Co">{{cite web|title=The 2015 Innovation By Design Awards Winners: Product Design|url=http://www.fastcodesign.com/3049908/innovation-by-design/the-2015-innovation-by-design-awards-winners-product-design|website=fastcodesign.com|publisher=Fast Company|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref> * [[Core77]] 2015 Design Awards<ref name="Core77 Award">{{cite web|title=goTenna |url=http://designawards.core77.com/Consumer-Products/33955/goTenna |website=core77.com |publisher=Core77 |accessdate=27 October 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveu