{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Hotel Hell | image = Hotel Hell.png | genre = [[Reality television]] | creator = [[Gordon Ramsay]] | developer = [[Mark Burnett]] | starring = [[Gordon Ramsay]] | theme_music_composer = [[Gordon Ramsay]] | opentheme = "[[Guilty Until Proven Insane|Hotel Hell]]" by [[Skyhooks (band)|Skyhooks]] ''(Seasons 1-2)'' | country = United States | language = English | num_seasons = 3 | num_episodes = 22 | list_episodes = #Episodes | executive_producer = {{Plainlist| * Adeline Ramage Rooney * Ben Adler * Gordon Ramsay * Patricia Llewellyn }} | camera = [[Panasonic]] [[Samsung]] | runtime = 43 minutes | company = One Potato Two Potato Endemol inc. Ramsay studios | distributor = [[Endemol]] | network = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] | picture_format = [[720p]] ([[HDTV]]) | audio_format = [[Dolby Digital|Dolby Digital 5.1]] | first_aired = {{Start date|2012|8|13}} | last_aired = {{End date|2016|7|26}} | related = | website = http://www.fox.com/hotelhell | production_website = }}
'''''Hotel Hell''''' is an [[United States|American]] [[reality television]] series created, hosted and narrated by [[Gordon Ramsay]], which ran on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] network for three seasons from 2012<ref name=EW092111>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2011/09/21/showbiz/tv/gordon-ramsay-hotel-hell-ew/index.html|title=Gordon Ramsay scores new Fox reality show: 'Hotel Hell'|work=CNN.com|date=September 21, 2011|accessdate=August 15, 2012}}</ref> to 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/hotel-hell-gordon-ramsay-fox-season-3-renewed|title=Gordon Ramsay's 'Hotel Hell' Renewed by Fox for Season 3|last=Maglio|first=Tony|publisher=The Wrap|date=August 17, 2015|accessdate=September 18, 2015}}</ref> It aired on Monday nights at 8 pm ET/PT.<ref name=Deadline061112>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/06/gordon-ramsays-fox-series-hotel-hell-to-premiere-in-august|title='Hotel Hell' Premiere In August – Gordon Ramsay's Fox Series Debut|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=Deadline.com|date=June 11, 2012|accessdate=August 15, 2012}}</ref> It was Ramsay's fourth series for the Fox network.
The series features Ramsay visiting various struggling lodging establishments throughout the United States in an attempt to reverse their misfortunes, following a similar concept established in Ramsay's other programs, ''[[Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares]]'' and its American counterpart, ''[[Kitchen Nightmares]]''.<ref name=EW092111/>
==Broadcast== Originally scheduled to premiere on Fox at 8 pm ET/PT on Friday, April 6, 2012,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2012/02/house-series-finale-hotel-hell-premiere|title=House Series Finale Date, Hotel Hell Premiere|last=Masters|first=Megan|work=TVLine|date=February 10, 2012|accessdate=August 15, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/fox-gordon-ramsay-hotel-hell-premiere-kitchen-nightmares-289307|title=Fox Schedules Gordon Ramsay's 'Hotel Hell,' More Midseason Dates|first=Michael|last=O'Connell|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 10, 2012}}</ref> the series was first rescheduled to Monday, June 4, 2012 at 8 pm ET/PT,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/03/28/premiere-dates-announced-for-so-you-think-you-can-dance-hells-kitchen-masterchef-and-hotel-hell/126440|first=Amanda|last=Kondolojy|title=Premiere Dates Announced for 'So You Think You Can Dance', 'Hell's Kitchen', 'MasterChef' and 'Hotel Hell'|work=TV by the Numbers|date=March 28, 2012|accessdate=August 15, 2012}}</ref> in order to accommodate the move of ''[[The Finder (U.S. TV series)|The Finder]]'' to Fridays,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/03/02/the-finder-moves-to-fridays-on-april-6/122807|title="The Finder" Moves To Fridays On April 6, 'Hotel Hell' Premiere Pushed To Summer|first=Bill|last=Gorman|work=TV by the Numbers|date=March 2, 2012|accessdate=August 15, 2012}}</ref> then rescheduled to August 13,<ref name=Deadline061112/> due to Ramsay's other two series, ''[[Hell's Kitchen (U.S. TV series)|Hell's Kitchen]]'' and ''[[MasterChef (US TV series)|MasterChef]]'', being scheduled for Monday nights during the summer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/fox-pushes-hotel-hell-premiere-to-late-summer|title=Fox Pushes 'Hotel Hell' Premiere To Late Summer|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=Deadline.com|date=May 1, 2012|accessdate=August 15, 2012}}</ref>
The series' first season, which consisted of six episodes, ended on September 3, 2012.<ref name=HOT-103&106>{{cite web|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/listings/20120820fox01|title=(HOT-103/6) "River Rock Inn/Roosevelt Hotel"|work=Listings – Hotel Hell on Fox|publisher=the Futon Critic|accessdate=August 22, 2012}}</ref> On August 31, 2012, Fox renewed ''Hotel Hell'' for a second season,<ref>{{cite web|first=James|last=Hibberd|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/08/31/hotel-hell-renewed|title=Fox renews Gordon Ramsay's 'Hotel Hell' for second season|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 31, 2012|accessdate=September 1, 2012}}</ref> which premiered on July 21, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://community.ew.com/2014/07/21/hotel-hell-recap-episode-one/|title='Hotel Hell' recap: Gordon Ramsay wishes he could turn back time|work=ew.com|accessdate=July 22, 2014}}</ref>
