{{about|the website|the operating system feature|Icon bar}} {{Italic title}} {{Notability|Web|date=June 2011}} {{infobox website | logo = The icon bar logo.png | screenshot = | collapsible = | collapsetext = | caption = | url = {{URL|iconbar.com}} | slogan = | commercial = No | type = | registration = Optional | language = English | owner = One Point Nought | author = Tim Fountain, Alasdair Bailey, Richard Goodwin<ref name="iconbar.com staff (2000)" /> | revenue = | alexa = | logocaption = | content license = | launch date = {{Start date and age|2000}}<ref name="Archive April 2011"> {{ citation | last = Johnson | first = Trevor | author-link = | publication-date = |date= April 2011 | title = Meet Jeffrey Lee | periodical = [[Archive (magazine)|Archive]] | series = | publication-place = | place = | publisher = Abbey Press | location = Glastonbury | volume = | issue = | pages = 14–18 | page = | at = | url = | archiveurl = | archivedate = | issn = | pmid = | pmc = | doi = | oclc = 222434223 | accessdate = | quote = The Icon Bar was started in 2000 as a spin-off to the (then popular) Acorn Arcade. [...] I think I only became properly involved with [The Icon Bar] sometime in 2006, when the Acorn Arcade content was merged in. | postscript = | ref = }}</ref> | current status = Online | footnotes = }}
'''''The Icon Bar''''' (also referred to as '''''TIB''''') is a [[computing]] and [[technology]] [[website]] with a focus on the [[RISC OS]] computer [[operating system]].
== History ==
''The Icon Bar'' was founded in 2000 by Tim Fountain, Alasdair Bailey and Richard Goodwin.<ref name="iconbar.com staff (2000)">{{ cite web | url = http://www.iconbar.com/staff/ | title = About The Icon Bar | accessdate = 2011-05-16 | last = | first = | work = The Icon Bar | publisher = [[One Point Nought]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000919123721/http://www.iconbar.com/staff/ | archivedate = 2000-09-19 | quote = Tim Fountain Founder member and designer of TIB [...] Richard Goodwin Along with Tim, Rich is a founder member of The Icon Bar [...] }}</ref><ref name="tfountain.co.uk">{{Cite web|title=Past projects|url=http://tfountain.co.uk/projects|first=Tim|last=Fountain|accessdate=2012-08-01|work=Personal website of Tim Fountain}}</ref> In 2004, co-founder Richard Goodwin was nominated for the ''[[Drobe]]'' awards for keeping the "popular forum" online.<ref name="drobe awards 2004">{{cite web | url=http://www.drobe.co.uk/article.php?id=1234 | title=Voting for Best of 2004 Awards open | work=[[Drobe]] | date=December 10, 2004 | accessdate=April 10, 2012 | author=Williams, Chris}}</ref> It was further developed by the same people who developed ''[[Acorn Arcade]]'',<ref name="iconbar.com about">{{ cite web | url = http://www.iconbar.com/about/ | title = About The Icon Bar | accessdate = 2011-05-16 | last = | first = | work = The Icon Bar | publisher = [[One Point Nought]] | quote = The Icon Bar [...] [s]tarted by the guys behind Acorn Arcade [...] }}</ref> the contents of which were incorporated in 2006.<ref name="Archive April 2011"/> At this time, it broadened its remit to also cover alternative platforms and new technologies, while still keeping abreast of the {{nowrap|RISC OS}} scene.<ref name="iconbar 206">{{cite web | url=http://iconbar.com/forums/viewthread.php?threadid=9695 | title=Icon Bar and Acorn Arcade relaunch | publisher=The Icon Bar | date=November 26, 2006 | accessdate=March 13, 2012 | author=The Icon Bar team}}</ref>
When ''[[Drobe]]'' closed as a news site in 2009, ''The Icon Bar'' was cited as a notable alternative<ref>{{ cite web | url = http://www.osnews.com/story/22203/Drobe_Closes_Its_Doors_After_Ten_Years | title = Drobe Closes Its Doors After Ten Years | accessdate = 2011-05-16 | last = Camen | first = Kroc | date = 2009-09-21 | work = OSnews | publisher = [[OSNews]] | quote = There are still a number of RISC OS related news sites, particularly notable iconbar.com [...] }}</ref><ref>{{ cite web | url = http://www.osnews.com/story/22459/What_Is_the_Point_of_RISCOS_Ltd_/ | title = What Is the Point of RISCOS Ltd? | accessdate = 2011-06-14 | last = Camen | first = Kroc | date = 2009-11-08 | work = OSnews | publisher = [[OSNews]] | quote = [...] leading RISC OS news website - The Icon Bar [...] }}</ref> and took over running the annual awards scheme for the {{nowrap|RISC OS}} scene.<ref name="iconbar.com awards">{{ cite web | url = http://www.iconbar.com/articles/Nominations_open_for_the_sDrobes_Icon_Bar_awards_2009/index1240.html | title = Nominations open for the <s>Drobe</s> Icon Bar awards 2009 | accessdate = 2011-06-13 | last = Lee | first = Jeffrey | work = The Icon Bar | publisher = [[One Point Nought]] | quote = For the past several years Drobe have run their yearly Drobe awards, in which members of the public nominate and vote for the RISC OS products and people who they believe have best served the platform over the course of the year. After a quick check with Drobe foreman Chris Williams to make sure he wasn't planning on running the awards this year, the staff at TIB decided it would be a good idea if we picked up the metaphorical torch and ran the awards ourselves. }}</ref> It has been selected for inclusion by editors in at least one [[web directory]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://botw.org/new/all/07202009.cfm | title = What's New - All Sites Added 7/20/2009 | accessdate = 2011-06-04 | date = 2009-07-20 | work = Best of the Web | publisher = [[Best of the Web Directory]] | quote = Icon Bar - RISC OS portal featuring news, discussions, polls, reviews, tutorials, and downloads.}}</ref>
== Content ==
The site features {{nowrap|RISC OS}} articles, news, forums and other media. It also hosts a ''Media Watch'' page, where users can share any relevant items they spot in the media.<ref name="iconbar media watch">{{cite web | url=http://www.iconbar.com/news/mediawatch.html | title=Media Watch | publisher=One Point Nought | work=The Icon Bar | accessdate=January 9, 2012}}</ref>
